724900f-a.title: Manhattan: York Avenue - 70th Street
724900f-a.text:
1314-1318-13222 York Avenue (Avenue A), at and adjoining N.E. corner
of 70th Street. 1314 was built around 1905 on the site of the
Davis Moulding Mill (1895). 1318 is old 1318-20 remodelleo. 1322
was built around 1895, as a cigar factory, and used around 1916
by the American Tobacco Company. These buildings are all about
to be demolished; and their place will be taken by some of the
new New York Hospital and Cornell Medical School buildingai a
laboratory and the Nurses' Home.
February 13, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
